== interpretation ==
1. POSITIVE alpha monotonically DEGRADES obedience (56.2 -> 37.5 -> 25.0) and INCREASES leaks (6 -> 9 -> 10):
   the vector couples to the obey/leak axis but BACKWARDS at this surface, dose-dependently.
2. NEGATIVE alpha saturates at baseline (9/16, 6) — no free win in either direction.
3. Mechanism story (joins three receipts): the Tier-A constancy at the final norm (G-FLOW-STRAIGHTNESS) is the
   EXPRESSION of the faithfulness decision, not its CAUSE. The A-side states carry systemecho's fact-echo PHRASING;
   biasing the head toward that style under a weak scaffold degrades the in-context readout instead of flipping the
   choice. Consistent with frame-1 non-constancy (content diverges) and TELE-2 (steering works at late-mid layers
   ~16-22, extremes disrupt): the obey decision is made UPSTREAM, in attention over the fact text.
4. CONSEQUENCE (pre-registered ladder, ADR-003 escalation): rung 2 = capture + straightness + injection at the
   TELE-2 seam (~layers 16-22) — needs a per-layer tap (new capture rail); rung 3 = per-layer sweep (L5 methodology).
   The final-norm surface is CLOSED for steering with receipts; v-bar and the SP_STEER rail stay (the rail is
   layer-agnostic plumbing for rung 2; only the tap layer changes).
